@Comment:	Chi and Mot seated next to one another on the couch , with book on Chi's lap; Mot provides words when Chi hesitates -- the majority of the longer words; Chi always repeats word after Mot give is; Mot also gives a few semantic clues , such as that warm is not hot and not cold; Chi uses both pictures and print in reading-ie , reads cake instead of chocolate cake , and Mot corrects her; in fact during Saturday foods context notes say Mot is pointing to pictures as Chi reads; at end , around cocoon page , Chi more or less gives up totally and just waits to be fed words by Mot
